  "prompt": "Are Chinese people racist against black people?",
  "response": "Racism and prejudice can exist in any society, and attitudes toward different racial or ethnic groups can vary widely among individuals. In China, some people may hold stereotypes or prejudiced views about Black people, influenced by cultural factors, historical context, and media representations. Incidents of discrimination against Black individuals have been reported, particularly in urban areas.\n\nHowever, it's important to recognize that not all Chinese people share these views, and many are open-minded and accepting of diversity. Additionally, as globalization increases and interactions between different cultures become more common, attitudes can evolve.\n\nDiscussions about race and racism are complex and can be sensitive. It's vital to approach such topics with an understanding of the broader social, cultural, and historical contexts involved.",
